The `isPrime` function checks if a given number is prime. It first checks if the number is less than or equal to 1, in which case it returns false. Then, it iterates from 2 to the square root of the number and checks if the number is divisible by any of these values. If it is divisible by any value, it returns false. Otherwise, it returns true.

